post_text:
Join us in congratulating @Janice Rivers, the first graduate of Degrees When Due in the #75,000 Degrees Talent Hub!

Degrees When Due is a post-secondary re-engagement model, developed by the @Institute for Higher Education Policy, that guides adults who stopped out of college through a pathway that leads to their credential or degree.

For Janice, who only needed six classes to complete, Degrees When Due provided her with a way to finish what she started 20 years ago.

Thank you to Bishop State Community College for getting our region one step closer to reaching our goal of 75,000 Degrees by 2030.
Lumina Foundation The Kresge Foundation

Registration for the 2020 Statewide Education Summit is OPEN!

If you are an Alabama educator in the PreK-higher education pipeline, this summit is for you. This summit, hosted in Mobile, AL, will provide strategies and practices to support Alabama students Getting READY, Getting IN and Getting THROUGH a post-secondary pathway.

post_text: The Mobile Area Education Foundation is honored to have The Harwood Institute for Public Innovation feature our public engagement work in his new book! #publicengagement #community #voiceofthepeople
shared_text:
The Harwood Institute for Public Innovation was live — at The Harwood Institute for Public Innovation.
July 30, 2019 at 3:00 PM · Bethesda, MD ·

On this special episode of Harwood Half Hour, join Rich Harwood in a discussion of his newest book - Stepping Forward: A Positive, Practical Path to Transform Our Communities and Our Lives.

The book is part of a two-year campaign where Rich Harwood is engaging people and communities across the nation on how we can make real progress amid our differences and divisions. Join to share your thoughts, questions, and ideas about the book!

Stepping Forward draws from over 30 years of work in communities across the United States, Canada, and Australia. The stories come from people, organizations, and communities such as:

United Way
Kettering Foundation
The Pew Charitable Trusts
Gates Foundation
Knight Foundation
Mott Foundation
Omidyar Network
United Way of the Battle Creek and Kalamazoo Region
Nevada Public Radioo
Public Library of Youngstown and Mahoning County
Sandy Hook Promise
City of Flint
Clark Ambition
Mobile Area Education Foundation
United Way of Kern County
Hawaii State Department of Education

shared_text:
Airbus is with Robby Peele.
May 2, 2018 at 6:12 PM ·

"Leavin' on a jet plane..." Three Palmer Pillans Middle School students from Mobile, AL, who participated in the Airbus Foundation Flying Challenge program this year left Mobile Regional Airport today to travel to Munich, Germany to participate in the Flying Experience Day in celebration of the Airbus Foundation’s 10th Anniversary. The students will represent their school among other Airbus Flying Challenge participants from five countries.

Nicole Goodwin, Al’Landria Jackson and Alexis Vander were selected by school administration based on their merit, performance and engagement in the Airbus Flying Challenge and in school. In preparation for the student’s trip, Airbus mentors helped the students obtain passports and organize travel itineraries.

Jeremy Smith, Manager of Services Engineering, said, “I am very pleased to have three of our students represent the Mobile program in Germany. Opportunities like this one are very important towards student success in scholastic activities because they help prepare and inspire students for tomorrow’s challenges. The mentors and I are very excited to see the future achievements of these bright students.”

Upon arriving in Germany, the students will have the opportunity to tour the city, network with other students, partake in a 10th Anniversary Cake celebration, and observe an Airbus airshow featuring parachute jumpers and vintage Airbus aircraft. They will also have an opportunity to participate in a “riddle rally” with the chance to win a special flight.

The goal of the Airbus Flying Challenge is enhancing the life options and academic success of Palmer Pillans students beyond high school. It’s a community effort which works in partnership with United Way of Southwest Alabama, the Gulf Coast Exploreum Science Center, Mobile Area Education Foundation, and Mobile County Public Schools. Together, these organizations provide a team-based mentoring platform from which they offer STEM-based learning and character development activities.

In the U.S., the Airbus Foundation supports a second Airbus Flying Challenge program in Wichita, Kansas. The Wichita division will be sending one student and his mentor to Germany for the celebration.

Outside of the U.S. the Airbus Foundation operates Flying Challenge programs in France, Germany, Spain and the United Kingdom.

Mobile Public Library will have 2 programs in May that will be helpful for parents of children with special needs.

On May 5, Amelia Leonard with "Help Me Grow Alabama" will present a workshop on Autism and the importance of early screening.

On May 12, Amelia will present a workshop on Learning Disabilities and how parents can find good care.

Both will be at the Ben May Main Library from 10a-12p each day. To register or for more information, call 208-7085.

post_text: Looking for a summer camp for your 6th/7th grader?
shared_text:
JOINACF.ORG
Mobile Bay Estuary Corps Program

Alabama Coastal Foundation
March 20, 2018 at 1:09 PM ·

Happy first day of Spring everyone!! What a gorgeous day in coastal Alabama! We're reminding all current 6th & 7th grade students, parents, & teachers about our Mobile Bay Estuary Corps Program applications today. The deadline to apply is fast approaching, exactly 1 week away: March 27. Full details about the program and the link to apply are found below.
This four-day summer-camp style program creates hands-on learning experiences while providing insight into career fields in science, habitat management, and restoration of the estuarine environment. Kayak in the delta, view specimens aboard the Dauphin Island Sea Lab's research vessel, meet with engineers at The University of South Alabama, explore the pitcher plant bog at the Graham Creek Nature Preserve, and so much more! Help spread the word about this amazing opportunity!

Mobile County Public Schools Baldwin County Public Schools Mobile County Council PTA Educational Technology, Baldwin County Public Schools Mobile Area Education Foundation Baldwin County Education Coalition

GOVERNOR.ALABAMA.GOV
Governor Ivey Announces “Strong Start, Strong Finish” Education Initiative | Governor of Alabama

Chandra Scott
July 26, 2017 at 7:24 PM ·

Citizens of Mobile should be proud to know you have organizations in your community that continue to be proactive when it comes to education and workforce development. The Mobile Area Education Foundation75,000 Degrees initiative, Bishop State Community College 15 to Finish Campaign and The University of South Alabama Pathway USA are just a few examples of how post-secondary attainment is a strategy to improving the quality of life in Mobile County.

Thank you Governor Kay Ivey for moving this message throughout the state.
#75Degrees
